  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Assistant Project Manager",
  "description": "<p>Requirements:</p>\n<p>-Candidate must possess at least Diploma/Advanced/Higher/Graduate Diploma in Interior Design or equivalent.</p>\n<p>-Preferable with 3 Year(s) of working experience in the related field is required for this position.</p>\n<p>-Entry level candidates are welcome to apply.</p>\n<p>-Preferably Junior Executive specialized in Interior Design.</p>\n<p>-5.5 days work week.</p>\n<p>-Good interpersonal and communication skills.</p>\n<p>Responsibilities:</p>\n<p>(a) Manage all phases and aspects of the project to ensure completion on time.</p>\n<p>(b) Provide support to site staffs.</p>\n<p>(c) Prepare documentation in related to project.</p>\n<p>(d) Prepare and attend progress meetings</p>\n<p>(e) Coordinate and liaise with all parties in the project team, including authorities, consultants, sub-contractors, suppliers, etc.</p>\n<p>(f) Lead the site team on project execution, safety matters, and project budgets control, etc.</p>\n<p>(g) Any other ad-hoc duties as required.</p>\n<p>Please indicate the below information in your resume:</p>\n<p>-Current &amp; Expected salary</p>\n<p>-Reason(s) for leaving</p>\n<p>-Availability to commence work</p>\n<p>-Relevant job experience</p>\n<p>Advantages:</p>\n<p>-Transport allowance</p>\n<p>-Handphone allowance</p>\n<p>-Personal growth</p>\n<p>* We regret to inform that only shortlisted applicants will be notified *</p>",
